    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I cannot think of any global data at this point. Can you think of anything?\r\n\r\nChain specific:\r\n- block/state (one for lightchain and one for full chain) \r\n- private keys for accounts\r\n- P2P node's private key (used to generate the node's unique ID and for authentication)\r\n- peer statistics\r\n\r\nSince all of that is actually _data_ (and not user-maintained _config_) generated/updated by py-evm, I believe it should go under _$XDG_DATA_HOME_ (which defaults to _$HOME/.local/share_).\r\n\r\nAs for the directory structure, I think the following would be a good start:\r\n\r\n```\r\n├── py-evm\r\n│   └── mainnet\r\n│       ├── chain         # LevelDB\r\n│       ├── keys          # KeyStore, whatever format we chose\r\n│       ├── lightchain    # LevelDB\r\n│       ├── nodekey       # a text file containing the node's P2P private key\r\n│       └── peers         # LevelDB\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat also leaves room for any global data to be stored directly under _$XDG_DATA_HOME/py-evm_",
